
All structures have dynamic capabilities;

Layer 0 : Resizeable Container;
    - Resizable array of consecutive values of a particular typename;
    - MUSTN'T BE USED TO CONTAIN objects; Objects are stored by pointer, or in an array of fixed size;
    - DOESN'T take instantiation or deletion in charge;


Layer 1 : type Container : resizeable container of primitive types;

    - Can add / set / remove elements by index
    - Can access elements anywhere;


Layer 2 : Object Container : resizeable container of object pointers ;

    - Container of object pointers;
    - Takes creation and deletion in charge;

     - Can add / set / remove elements by index
     - Can access elements anywhere;
